# A. Inheritance

```
public class Person : Animal {
  public void buy() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;c&quot;); }
}

public class Animal {
  public void go() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;go&quot;); }
  public void jump() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;jump&quot;); }
}

```

Please check out [Inheritance (C# Programming Guide)](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/programming-guide/classes-and-structs/inheritance)

----

Update. Technically the Animal can have a person. If it&#39;s a good design is a different question.

```
public class Person : Animal {}

public class Animal
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public Person Person { get; set; }
}


class Program
{
    public static void Main()
    {
        var p = new Person() { Name = &quot;Prince&quot; }; 
        var a = new Animal() { Person = p, Name = &quot;Kenley Lass&quot; };

        Console.WriteLine(a.Person.Name);
        // prints: My name is Prince
    }
}
```

# B. Independent types with helpers

Here&#39;s something that may be to your taste that doesn&#39;t involve inheritance and fits your idea.

```
public class Person
{
    
    public void buy() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;buy&quot;); }

    private string destination = &quot;Not set yet&quot;;
    // Person&#39;s go() doesn&#39;t need a destination, they can decide for themselves 
    public void go() =&gt; Helpers.go(destination);
    public void jump() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;jump&quot;); }
}

public class AimlessAnimal
{
    public void go(string destination) =&gt; Helpers.go(destination);
    public void jump() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;jump&quot;); }
}


public class Elephant
{
    public void go(string destination) =&gt; Helpers.go(destination);
    // elephant&#39;s cant jump :(
}

// This doesn&#39;t have to be a separate class, it can be part of AimlessAnimal
public static class Helpers
{
    public static void go(string destination) { Console.WriteLine($&quot;going to {destination}&quot;); }
    public static void jump() { Console.WriteLine(&quot;jump&quot;); }
}
```

